;; tsukuru 作 — curated heuristic HS (Harmonized System) chapter/heading classification
;; table. Documented/reviewable data source for `classify-product` in
;; src/tsukuru/kotoba/agent.cljc — the .cljc embeds this same data as a Clojure literal
;; (HS-CLASSIFICATION-TABLE) so the actor stays IO-free / portable to cljs+WASM (no
;; runtime file read, no new deps). Keep the two in sync by hand when editing either one.
;;
;; Scope: a SMALL curated snapshot covering tsukuru's actual manufacturing verticals per
;; CLAUDE.md and manifest.edn — CNC/metal machining, aluminium/steel/
;; plastics articles, electronics/communication equipment, semiconductor devices,
;; EUV/optical-precision instruments (EUV vertical), CNT/carbon-fiber (CNT fiber
;; vertical), textiles, vehicle parts, radar/navigation. This is NOT an authoritative
;; customs ruling and NOT a full HS nomenclature — real tariff classification requires a
;; real classifier/host integration (inject `classify-fn` at the call site).
;;
;; Shape: a vector of {"hsCode" <chapter/heading> "description" <text> "keywords"
;; [<capability-like phrase> ...]}. A product description is matched by tokenizing it the
;; same way `capability-match`/`tokens` do in agent.cljc, then scoring how many keyword
;; phrases in an entry share a token with the description; the highest-scoring entry
;; (score > 0) wins. No match → an honest "unclassified" result (see classify-product),
;; never a silent fixed-code fallback.
